{\f0\fs36\b Welcome to Geniuz\b0}\par
\pard\sa120\sl320\slmult1
{\f0\fs24\cf2 Your AI agents forget everything between sessions.\line Geniuz fixes that. Three commands. Local. Private. Instant.}\par

\pard\sa200\sl320\slmult1
{\f0\fs26\b To install}\par
{\f0\fs24 Open {\i Install Geniuz.pkg} and follow the prompts.}\par

{\f0\fs26\b What gets installed}\par
{\f0\fs24
\bullet  {\b geniuz} CLI \emdash  available in your terminal immediately\line
\bullet  {\b Geniuz} menu bar app \emdash  launches from Applications\line
\bullet  {\b Claude Desktop} integration \emdash  auto-configured, ready to use}\par

{\f0\fs26\b After install, try this}\par
{\f1\fs22 geniuz remember -c "first memory: geniuz is installed and working"\line geniuz recall "first memory"}\par
{\f0\fs24 If your memory comes back, everything works.}\par

{\f0\fs26\b Three commands. That\rquote s all.}\par
{\f0\fs24
\bullet  {\f1 geniuz remember} \emdash  save what matters\line
\bullet  {\f1 geniuz recall} \emdash  find it by meaning\line
\bullet  {\f1 geniuz recent} \emdash  see what\rquote s new}\par

{\f0\fs22\cf2 Your data stays on your Mac. No cloud. No account. No telemetry.\line
Questions? hello@mvara.ai}\par
